com.tomscz.afswinx.component

Class AFSwinx

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomscz.afswinx.component.AFSwinx

  • public class AFSwinx
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is facade to using AFSwinx. Use getInstance to get unique instance in your application. It also hold information about localization see enableLocalization(ResourceBundle) and with skin see setApplicationSkin(Skin) for more information.
    Since:
    1.0.0.
    Author:
    Martin Tomasek (martin@toms-cz.com)

      • addComponent

        public void addComponent(AFSwinxTopLevelComponent componentToAdd,
                java.lang.String key)
        This method add component to current hash map, which hold all components which could be retrieved by this class. If there exists components with the same key then component is removed and the new one is added.
        Parameters:
        componentToAdd - which will be add.
        key - under it will be add. This key also could be used to retrieve this component.

      • getExistedComponent

        public AFSwinxTopLevelComponent getExistedComponent(java.lang.String componentKey)
        This method return component by key. If component was not added before then it null is returned.
        Parameters:
        componentKey - key of component which will be retrieve.
        Returns:
        component whose key is equal to componentKey which is received as parameter. Null if component does not exist.

      • removeComponent

        public void removeComponent(java.lang.String key)
        This method remove component from hash map based on key.
        Parameters:
        key - of component which will be removed.

      • removeAllComponents

        This method remove all component which were created.

      • getLocalization

        public java.util.ResourceBundle getLocalization()

      • enableLocalization

        public void enableLocalization(java.util.ResourceBundle localization)
        This method set localization which is used to during building components. This localization is more important then default localization but less important then concrete localization on component. It localize labels and validation messages.
        Parameters:
        localization - bundle which will be used. Could be null if null, then default localization is used.
